 lyrics. Through these textual networks, Callaci shows how youth migrants and urban intellectuals in Dar es Salaam fashioned a collective ethos of postcolonial African citizenship. This spirit ushered in a revolution rooted in the city and its networks—an urban revolution that arose in spite of the nation-state's pro-rural ideology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCity and town lifexSocial aspectszTanzaniazDar es Salaamy20th century. 0aCity and town lifezTanzaniazDar es SalaamxHistoryy20th century. 0aIntellectualszTanzaniazDar es SalaamxHistoryy20th century. 0aUrbanizationzTanzaniazDar es SalaamxHistoryy20th century. 70(DE-601)1044612250(DE-588)4274490-8aGeistesleben2gnd 70(DE-601)1044670530(DE-588)4027249-7aIntellektueller2gnd 70(DE-601)1060796970(DE-588)4077587-2aSozialer Wandel2gnd 70(DE-601)1061286980(DE-588)4063234-9aVerstädterung2gnd 70(DE-601)2158246600(DE-588)4424590-7aStadtleben2gnd 70(DE-601)70019066X0(DE-588)7502135-3aStadtkultur2gnd 7aHISTORY / Africa / East.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106963490 cprintz978082236984440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372325423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822372325/original  a978-3-11-069634-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles